Package: MSTest
Type: Package
Title: MSTest: An R-package For Testing Markov-Switching Models
Version: 1.0
Date: 2019-08-15
Author: Gabriel Rodriguez Rondon,
    Jean-Marie Dufour
Maintainer: Gabriel Rodriguez  <gabriel.rodriguezrondon@mcgill.ca>
Description: This package allows the user to test the null hypothesis of a linear model against
    the alternative of a markov switching model. The package includes Likelihood Ratio (LR) 
    type tests (Hansen 1996), The optimal test for markov switching parameters proposed by
    Carrasco et al. (2014), and the moment based test proposed by Dufour & Luger (2017).
License: MIT
Imports: GenSA, GA, pso, multiway, Rcpp (>= 1.0.1), RcppArmadillo
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo, multiway, GenSA, GA, pso
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Depends: 
    R (>= 2.10)
Encoding: UTF-8
